text.tspan: Total confirmed COVID-19 deaths per million: how rapidly are they
Shown are the total confirmed deaths per million people. Limited testing and challenges in the attribution of the cause of death
means that the number of confirmed deaths may not be an accurate count of the true number of deaths from COVID-19.
Days since total confirmed deaths reached 0.1 per million
Source: European CDC – Situation Update Worldwide – Last updated 28th April, 11:30 (London time)
